com.serena.dmclient.api
Class DimensionsConnectionDetails

java.lang.Object
  com.serena.dmclient.api.DimensionsConnectionDetails
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable
public class DimensionsConnectionDetails
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable

Concrete class that encapsulates the details needed to create a connection to a Dimensions server, the DimensionsConnection class. Instances of this class can be created and passed to DimensionsConnectionManager.getConnection() in order to get a DimensionsConnection.

See Also:
DimensionsConnection, DimensionsConnectionManager.getConnection(DimensionsConnectionDetails)

getSSOToken

public java.lang.String getSSOToken()
The SSO (Single Sign On) Token to be used when connecting to Dimensions. This defines the user's identity and roles when connected. When defined the User & Password parameters are ignored. If Token contains dbName, dbConn claims/parameters itself the corresponding parameters in the connection details can be skipped.

Returns:
the currently configured SSO Token.
See Also:
setSSOToken(String)

getCertificateProver

public AuthCertificateProver getCertificateProver()
This interface is required to prove certificate authenticity in case when login by Certificate is used. When client connects to server this callback will be called to sign data by certificate's private key, this data will be verified on server using certificate's public key.

Returns:
the currently configured user Certificate (usually X.509).

setCertificateProver(AuthCertificateProver)

getServer

public java.lang.String getServer()
The Dimensions server's hostname to connect to. If the Dimensions listener is not on port 671, then the port number should be provided within the server name text separated by a colon character, e.g. "myserver:675" for a Dimensions server called myserver listening on port 675.

Returns:
the currently configured Dimensions server.
See Also:
